So here is the deal...

I know that I'll have to create like at least 4 or 5 conceptual spaces for "apple". I know color will need to be one of them. It makes a lot of sense to start with color as the first space to model in conceptual space.
- Also I can work on the API and underlying language of conceptual spaces representation that I need to visualize anything. In short, I want the way I build this first conceptual space to be generic and reusable to the other representations that need to build.
- One great advantage is that not everything needs to be spot on. Once we start listing "truths" those "truths" will help correct and label the conceptual space.

- [x] [[visualize_a_conceptual_space_for_color.md]]

Here are the spaces we need...

